own sides of mixing bowl with spatula then chop again <b>5 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer to a bowl."},{"content":"Place a plate on mixing bowl lid, weigh on flour then remove plate. With wet hands, take 2 Tbsp prawn paste and shape into a ball. Coat with flour and flatten lightly into a patty. Place on a plate and dust with extra flour. Repeat until all mixture has been used (approx. 20 patties). Place in fridge for approx. 30 minutes."},{"content":"Heat vegetable oil in a frying pan over a medium heat, shallow fry patties for 5 minutes, turning halfway through, until golden brown. Transfer to paper towels to drain excess oil then serve warm with plum sauce."}],"hintsAndTricks":["These prawn patties are a perfect snack served with a cold drink such as lychee juice.","The plum sauce may be prepared in advance. It can be stored in the fridge for approx. <b>7-10 days<b> in an airtight container. This sauce goes well with seafood or white meat."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","1h 20m","20 pieces"]}